sophomore season as a Florida prep before moving in with a coach's family and turning his life around. Committed to then-head coach Steve Kragthorpe and the Cardinals in 2007 when he rushed 24 times for 187 yards (7.8-yard average) and two touchdowns with three receptions for 25 yards (8.3) and zero TDs. Injured his right knee against Pittsburgh and did not play against Syracuse.
